            {
                "comment": "Crenshaw was an okay professor at best. He was not very welcoming in lectures and spent 10 minutes of every lecture off topic. The lecture material was fairly easy to understand, however, the homework and quiz questions are written very oddly and it is hard to determine what they are asking of you. Unfortunately he is the only professor.",
                "difficulty_rating": 4,
                "quality_rating": 2
            },
            {
                "comment": "Tom is a great guy, I actually wish he was my grandpa. I highly suggest taking 415 with him.  He states the first day of class that if you come to class you will get an A.  Plus, the group research project is fun and you get to play with baby pigs!",
                "difficulty_rating": 1,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "I had Crenshaw for my InterAg 155 discussion adviser. He is a very knowledgeable man that is passionate about his work with swine nutrition. He is very easy to talk to and is willing to not just discuss class but also you and your goals and ambitions. One of the kindest an most interesting people I know.",
                "difficulty_rating": 1,
                "quality_rating": 5
